B — Zero-Shot Role_output:
A data processing agreement (DPA) should include key terms such as: 

1. Definition of personal data and special categories of data, if applicable; 
2. Description of the processing activities, including the purpose, duration, and scope of processing; 
3. Identification of the data controller and data processor, including their respective roles and responsibilities; 
4. Security and confidentiality obligations, including data protection by design and default, data breach notification, and data subject rights; 
5. Data transfer and international transfer mechanisms, including compliance with applicable data protection laws; 
6. Data subject rights, including access, rectification, erasure, and objection; 
7. Data processor's obligations to cooperate with data protection authorities and data subjects; 
8. Termination and return or deletion of personal data upon termination; 
9. Liability and indemnification provisions; and 
10. Governing law and dispute resolution mechanisms.
